This paper proposes a framework for building a hybrid predictive model that combines an interpretable model with a black-box model. The paper focuses on the trade-off between interpretability and predictive performance, which is a common concern in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the transparency of the model, which is related to fairness and accountability, suggesting that it could belong to cs.CE (Computers and Society) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
